
How to build and use js2mpl-vm

  1. cd to your work area and get source code from the following git repositories
     note all the steps assume you are in the work directory
      % git clone wenhu@10.213.64.15:/opt/git/maple/mapleall.git
      % git clone wenhu@10.213.64.15:/opt/git/maple/mozjs.git
      % git clone wenhu@10.213.64.15:/opt/git/maple/js2mpl-vm.git

     at this point, the directory structure should look like
       maple
         |- mapleall
              |- Makefile
              |- maplebe
              |- mapleir
              |- maplevm
              |- Mempool
         |- js2mpl-vm
              |- include
              |- Makefile
              |- Makefile.in
              |- README
              |- src
              |- tests
         |- mozjs
              |- Makefile
              |- mozjs-31.2.0
              |- README

  2. build mapleall (Mempool, mapleir, maplebe, maplevm)
      % cd mapleall; make

  3. build mozjs
      % cd mozjs; make config; make -j4

  4. build js2mpl-vm
      // this will acturally build mapleall as well as run regression tests
      % cd js2mpl-vm; make 

      // rebuild mapleall and js2mpl-vm
      % cd js2mpl-vm; make rebuild 

  5. run regression
      % cd js2mpl-vm/tests; make regression
      % cd js2mpl-vm/tests; make todo
